The paper deals with graph theory and algorithms for finding maximum independent sets in certain classes of graphs. The use of terms such as "hole", "pyramid", and "chordless paths" suggest that the paper is likely to be in the Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-category. The algorithmic nature of the paper and the focus on finding independent sets suggest that it could also be in the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The use of decomposition theorems and bounding techniques suggest that it could be in the Computational Geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The study of graph classes and their properties suggests that it could be in the Graph Theory (cs.GT) sub-category. Finally, the use of weighted independent sets suggests that it could be in the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
